metric.title: NHD
metric.description: The NHD (Normalized Hamming Distance) class cohesion metric is based on the "Hamming distance" from information theory. Here, we measure the similarity in all methods of a class in terms of the types of their arguments. A class in which all methods accept the same set of types of parameters is said to be in "perfect parameter agreement" (NHD score "1"), whereas a class in which all methods accept unique parameter types not shared by others has no parameter agreement (NHD score "0").
